Jim Morris

Jim Morris, Council Place 3

Email Jim Morris

elected to City Council Place 3 on June 7th, 2025. A Hutto resident since 2008, having grown up in North Austin. Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering and Master of Science in Engineering UT Austin; retired Semiconductor Process Technology Engineer.

After years of volunteering with the CoHutto Boards and Commissions, sought a new level of dedication as a CouncilMember to sustain and improve the Quality of Life for Hutto. As an Elected Official, CouncilMember prides himself on being a representative of all residents; within the city limits, working within the ETJ and working with the Hutto ISD.
